Yeah, you have a pumpkin.

158
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:50,674
Leave me alone.

159
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:52,600
Boys: He's gonna get you.
He's gonna get you.

160
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:56,634
He's gonna get you.
He's gonna get you.

161
00:16:56,799 --> 00:16:58,552
The boogeyman is coming.

162
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,836
- Leave me alone.
- He doesn't believe us.

163
00:17:01,039 --> 00:17:03,076
Don't you know what happens
on Halloween?

164
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:04,833
Yeah, we get candy.

165
00:17:05,039 --> 00:17:07,236
- ( laughs )
- The boogeyman.

166
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:10,596
The boogeyman. The boogeyman.
The boogeyman. The boogeyman.

167
00:17:10,799 --> 00:17:12,676
The boogeyman.

168
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:15,190
( Boys laughing )

169
00:17:22,839 --> 00:17:25,958
( breathing heavily )

170
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:52,108
( car starts )

171
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:45,993
He's on his way.

172
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,198
You've got to believe me, Officer.

173
00:18:49,359 --> 00:18:51,396
He is coming to Haddonfield.

174
00:18:51,559 --> 00:18:54,358
Because I know him.

175
00:18:54,519 --> 00:18:56,635
I'm his doctor.

176
00:18:56,799 --> 00:18:58,790
You must be ready for him.

177
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,398
If you don't,
it's your funeral.

178
00:19:01,559 --> 00:19:04,278
( Train crossing bell dinging )

179
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:07,478
( train whistle blowing )

180
00:19:54,039 --> 00:19:56,111
Girls: We're from Haddonfield,
couldn't be prouder.

181
00:19:56,279 --> 00:19:58,476
Can't hear us now,
we'll yell a little louder.

182
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,711
We're from Haddonfield,
couldn't be prouder.

183
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:03,519
Oh, look at you.
Look at all the books you have.

184
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,232
You need a shopping cart
to get home.

185
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,835
( laughs )

186
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,673
Girls: Yay, Haddonfield!

187
00:20:09,839 --> 00:20:12,638
Yeah, not funny.

188
00:20:12,799 --> 00:20:14,438
You know, it's totally insane.

189
00:20:14,599 --> 00:20:16,519
We have three new cheers
to learn in the morning.

190
00:20:16,559 --> 00:20:18,038
The game is in the afternoon.

191
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,559
I have to get my hair done at 5:00
and the dance is at 8:00.

192
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:22,000
I'll be totally wiped out.

193
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:23,388
I don't think you have
enough to do tomorrow.

194
00:20:23,559 --> 00:20:25,038
Totally.

195
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:31,830
As usual, I have nothing to do.

196
00:20:32,039 --> 00:20:34,759
It's your own fault and I don't
feel a bit sorry for you.

197
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,356
Hey, Lynda, Laurie.

198
00:20:38,519 --> 00:20:40,750
