199
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:43,877
We did. 15 minutes.
You totally never showed.

200
00:20:44,039 --> 00:20:45,552
That's not true. Here I am.

201
00:20:48,599 --> 00:20:50,161
What's wrong, Annie?
You're not smiling.

202
00:20:50,279 --> 00:20:52,077
I'm never smiling again.

203
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:54,834
Paul dragged me into
the boys' locker room.

204
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,751
Exploring uncharted territory?

205
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,911
- It's been totally charted.
- We just talked.

206
00:20:59,079 --> 00:21:00,433
Sure, sure.

207
00:21:00,599 --> 00:21:03,432
Old jerko got caught throwing
eggs and soaping windows.

208
00:21:03,599 --> 00:21:06,512
His parents grounded him.
He can't come over tonight.

209
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:08,119
Thought you were
babysitting tonight.

210
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,913
The only reason she babysits
is to have a place to...

211
00:21:10,119 --> 00:21:11,315
Shit.

212
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:14,393
I have a place for that.

213
00:21:14,559 --> 00:21:16,914
I forgot my chemistry book.

214
00:21:17,079 --> 00:21:19,594
So who cares?
I always forget my chemistry book,

215
00:21:19,759 --> 00:21:21,592
and my math book,
and my English book,

216
00:21:21,799 --> 00:21:23,393
and my, let's see,
my French book.

217
00:21:23,559 --> 00:21:25,436
Who needs books anyway?
I don't need books.

218
00:21:25,599 --> 00:21:27,272
I always forget all of my books.

219
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:30,192
I mean, it doesn't really matter
if you have your books or not.

220
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:34,992
Lynda:
Hey, isn't that Devon Graham?

221
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,197
I don't think so.

222
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,277
I think he's cute.

223
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,157
Hey, jerk.

224
00:21:45,359 --> 00:21:47,351
Speed kills.

225
00:21:47,519 --> 00:21:50,717
( Tires squeal )

226
00:21:57,759 --> 00:21:59,990
God, can't you take a joke?

227
00:22:07,319 --> 00:22:10,278
You know, Annie, someday you're
gonna get us all into deep trouble.

228
00:22:13,279 --> 00:22:14,509
Totally.

229
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:17,832
I hate a guy with a car
and no sense of humor.

230
00:22:20,559 --> 00:22:22,073
Well, are we still on
for tonight?

231
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:25,311
I wouldn't want to get you
in deep trouble, Lynda.

232
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:27,278
Oh, come on, Annie.

233
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:29,909
Bob and I have been
planning on it all week.

234
00:22:30,079 --> 00:22:31,433
All right.

235
00:22:31,599 --> 00:22:33,192
The Wallaces leave at 7:00.

236
00:22:33,359 --> 00:22:36,159
I'm babysitting the Doyles.
It's only three houses down.

237
00:22:36,319 --> 00:22:38,240
- We can keep each other company.
- Oh, terrific.

238
00:22:38,319 --> 00:22:41,199
I've got three choices...
watch the kid sleep,

239
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:44,272
listen to Lynda screw around,
or talk to you.

240
00:22:48,119 --> 00:22:50,111
Boy, I was so mad.

241
00:22:50,279 --> 00:22:52,476
( Chatter continues )

242
00:23:17,079 --> 00:23:18,558
Want to go buy your own?

243
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:21,472
