off of me, girl.

244
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,950
- What time tonight?
- I don't know yet.

245
00:23:24,119 --> 00:23:25,997
I have to get out of taking
my little brother trick-or-treating.

246
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:29,278
- Saving the treats for Bob?
- Funny. See ya.

247
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,157
- Bye.
- Bye.

248
00:23:44,079 --> 00:23:45,400
Annie, look.

249
00:23:45,559 --> 00:23:47,073
Look where?

250
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:49,277
Behind the bush.

251
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:51,192
I don't see anything.

252
00:23:51,359 --> 00:23:53,749
The man who drove by so fast,
that one you yelled at.

253
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:56,594
Subtle, isn't he?

254
00:24:03,319 --> 00:24:05,596
Hey, creep.

255
00:24:08,119 --> 00:24:09,792
Laufie, dean.

256
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:12,348
He wants to talk to you.

257
00:24:12,519 --> 00:24:14,829
He wants to take you
out tonight.

258
00:24:29,279 --> 00:24:30,792
He was standing right there.

259
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:32,633
Poor Laurie.

260
00:24:32,799 --> 00:24:34,871
Scared another one away.

261
00:24:35,039 --> 00:24:37,792
It's tragic. You never go out.

262
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:41,634
You must have a small fortune
stashed from babysitting so much.

263
00:24:41,799 --> 00:24:43,153
Guys think I'm too smart.

264
00:24:43,319 --> 00:24:45,038
I don't. I think you're wacko.

265
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:47,476
Now you're seeing men
behind bushes.

266
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,996
Well, home sweet home.

267
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:54,720
See you later.

268
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,472
- Bye.
- Bye.

269
00:25:05,759 --> 00:25:08,194
(wind blowing )

270
00:25:09,839 --> 00:25:11,432
( screams )

271
00:25:11,599 --> 00:25:12,828
Excuse me, Laurie.

272
00:25:12,974 --> 00:25:14,615
Oh, Mr. Brackett.
I'm sorry, Mr. Brackett.

273
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:16,869
- I didn't mean to startle you.
- That's all right.

274
00:25:17,039 --> 00:25:18,872
You know it's Halloween.

275
00:25:19,039 --> 00:25:21,039
I guess everyone's entitled
to one good scare, huh?

276
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:23,838
Yes, sir. Nice seeing you, sir.

277
00:25:46,119 --> 00:25:48,395
(girl laughs)

278
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:59,076
( laughter)

279
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,791
- Trick or treat.
- Trick or treat.

280
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:08,230
(children laughing)

281
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,152
Well, kiddo,

282
00:26:10,319 --> 00:26:12,913
I thought you outgrew
superstition.

283
00:26:26,119 --> 00:26:28,430
(wind blowing )

284
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:55,789
( phone ringing )

285
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:03,154
Hello?

286
00:27:03,319 --> 00:27:05,960
( Crunching )

287
00:27:06,119 --> 00:27:08,111
Hello?

288
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:11,996
Who is this?

289
00:27:16,559 --> 00:27:19,393
( Phone rings )

290
00:27:21,519 --> 00:27:22,634
Hello?

291
00:27:22,799 --> 00:27:24,153
Annie: Why'd you hang up on me?

292
00:27:24,319 --> 00:27:27,118
- Annie? Was that you?
- Of course.

293
00:27:27,279 --> 00:27:29,319
Why didn't you say anything?
You scared me to death.

294
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:31,391
I had my mouth full.
Couldn't you hear me?

295
00:27:31,559 --> 00:27:33,079
I thought it was
an obscene phone call.

296
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:35,197
Now you hear obscene chewing.

297
00:27:35,359 --> 00:27:37,589
- You're losing it, Laurie.
- I already lost it.

298
00:27:37,799 --> 00:27:39,153
I doubt that.

299
00:27:39,319 --> 00:27:41,039
Listen, my mother
is letting me use her car.

300
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,433
I'll pick you up at 6:30.

301
00:27:42,599 --> 00:27:44,636
- Okay, bye.
- Bye.

302
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:58,836
Just calm down.

303
00:28:00,079 --> 00:28:01,990
This is ridiculous.

304
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:20,308
- Hurry up.
- Hi.

305
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:22,949
( Music playing on radio )

306
00:29:29,119 --> 00:29:31,588
We just have time.

307
00:29:42,599 --> 00:29:45,114
Yeah, Judith Myers.

308
00:29:45,279 --> 00:29:46,713
Myers.

309
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:49,440
Row 18, plot 20.

310
00:29:51,079 --> 00:29:54,117
You know, every town
has something like this happen.

311
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:57,231
I remember over in Russellville,

312
00:29:57,440 --> 00:30:00,114
old Charlie Bowles
about 15 years ago,

313
00:30:00,279 --> 00:30:02,874
one night he finished dinner

314
00:30:03,039 --> 00:30:06,476
and he excused himself
from the table

315
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:08,676
and he went out to the garage

316
00:30:08,839 --> 00:30:12,628
and he got himself a hacksaw.

317
00:30:12,799 --> 00:30:14,790
And then he went
back into the house

318
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,719
and he kissed his wife and his
two children good-bye

319
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:19,637
and then he proceeded...

320
00:30:19,799 --> 00:30:21,871
- Where are we?
- Huh? Oh.

321
00:30:22,039 --> 00:30:23,951
It's right over here.

322
00:30:24,119 --> 00:30:27,317
Yeah, Myers. Judith Myers.
I remember her.

323
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:30,757
Couldn't believe it.
Such a young boy.

324
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:34,355
Are we lost?

325
00:30:34,559 --> 00:30:37,711
Why do they do it?
Goddamn kids.

326
00:30:39,839 --> 00:30:41,876
They'll do anything
for Halloween.

327
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:45,150
- Whose grave was it?
- Oh, I don't know.

328
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:48,836
18, 19...

329
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:53,076
Judith Myers.

330
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,711
He came home.

331
00:31:02,359 --> 00:31:03,919
Still spooked?

332
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:06,037
I wasn't spooked.

333
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:08,237
- Lies.
- I wasn't.

334
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,356
I saw somebody standing
in Mr. Riddle's backyard.

335
00:31:10,519 --> 00:31:12,829
- Probably Mr. Riddle.
- He was watching me.

336
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:16,709
Mr. Riddle was watching you?
Laurie, Mr. Riddle is 87.

337
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:19,712
- Laurie: He could still watch.
- It's probably all he can do.

338
00:31:21,079 --> 00:31:23,195
- What's the pumpkin for?
- I brought it for Tommy.

339
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:26,278
I figured carving a jack-o'-lantern
would keep him occupied.

340
00:31:26,440 --> 00:31:28,953
I always said you'd make
a fabulous Girl Scout.

341
00:31:29,119 --> 00:31:30,315
Thanks.

342
00:31:30,480 --> 00:31:33,000
For that matter, I might as well
be a Girl Scout myself tonight.

343
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:36,152
I plan on making popcorn
and watching Dr. Dementia.

344
00:31:36,319 --> 00:31:38,549
Six straight hours
of horror movies.

345
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:40,950
Little Lindsey Wallace
won't know what hit her.

346
00:31:41,119 --> 00:31:42,679
(coughing )

347
00:31:51,039 --> 00:31:53,919
My dad! Get rid of this.

348
00:31:54,079 --> 00:31:56,309
( Alarm ringing )

349
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,957
- ( coughing )
- Laurie, stop coughing.

350
00:32:04,095 --> 00:32:05,734
- What's the matter with you?
- Oh, Jesus.

351
00:32:05,759 --> 00:32:07,557
Annie: Just be natural.
There he is.

352
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:09,551
Just be natural, Laurie.

353
00:32:14,279 --> 00:32:15,952
Hi, Annie. Laurie.

354
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:18,878
Hi, Dad. What happened?

355
00:32:19,079 --> 00:32:20,912
- What?
- What happened?

356
00:32:21,119 --> 00:32:23,269
Oh, somebody broke into
the hardware store.

357
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,555
Probably kids.

358
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:27,314
You blame everything on kids.

359
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,356
All they took was
a Halloween mask,

360
00:32:29,519 --> 00:32:32,353
rope, and a couple of knives.
Who do you think it was?

361
00:32:32,519 --> 00:32:35,239
It's hard growing up
with a cynical father.

362
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:37,755
- Aren't you gonna be late?
- Huh?

363
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:40,036
- I said aren't you gonna be late?
- ( Alarm stops )

364
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:43,032
He shouts, too.

365
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:47,118
BVG, girls.

366
00:32:47,279 --> 00:32:49,191
- Bye, Dad.
- Bye.

367
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:58,957
Sheriff.

368
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:01,116
Pardon me, I'm Loomis.

369
00:33:01,279 --> 00:33:03,191
- Dr. Sam Loomis.
- Lee Brackett.

370
00:33:03,359 --> 00:33:05,079
I'd like to have a word
with you if I could.

371
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:06,513
May be a few minutes.
I've got to take care...

372
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:08,239
it is important.

373
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:10,675
- 10 minutes.
- I'll be here.

374
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:27,992
What's the matter with you?

375
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:30,470
I think he knew.
I'm sure he could smell it.

376
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:32,711
- No, he didn't.
- He did.

377
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,518
See the look on his face?

378
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:37,319
He always looks like that.

379
00:33:40,015 --> 00:33:42,055
What are you gonna wear
to the dance tomorrow night?

380
00:33:42,079 --> 00:33:44,640
I didn't know you thought
about things like that, Laurie.

381
00:33:51,519 --> 00:33:53,352
You know, you could
ask somebody.

382
00:33:53,519 --> 00:33:54,953
- No, I couldn't.
- Sure, you could.

383
00:33:55,119 --> 00:33:57,395
All you have to do is go
up to somebody and say,

384
00:33:57,559 --> 00:33:59,436
"You want to go to the dance?"

385
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:02,393
You could do that. I couldn't.

386
00:34:02,599 --> 00:34:05,876
Well, you could ask Dick Baxter.
He'd go out with you.

387
00:34:06,039 --> 00:34:09,157
I'd rather go out
with Ben Tramer.

388
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,833
Ben Tramer?

389
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:13,797
I knew it.

390
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:15,552
( laughs )

391
00:34:15,719 --> 00:34:18,757
So you do think
about things like that, huh, Laurie?

392
00:34:18,920 --> 00:34:20,273
Shut up.

393
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:22,829
He's cute. Ben Tramer.

394
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,434
Shh.

395
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:59,070
- Okay, see you later.
- Bye.

396
00:35:30,519 --> 00:35:33,876
Kids: Trick or treat, give me
something good to eat.

397
00:35:34,039 --> 00:35:37,795
Trick or treat, trick or treat,
give me something good to eat.

398
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:40,679
Trick or treat, trick or treat,
give me something...

399
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:51,237
( knocks )

400
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,512
- Hi.
- Man: Hi, Annie.

401
00:35:54,679 --> 00:35:56,478
- Come on in.
- How you doing tonight?

402
00:35:56,639 --> 00:35:58,994
Annie: What time do you
want her in bed?

403
00:35:59,159 --> 00:36:01,356
Woman: Be in bed by 9:00, okay?

404
00:36:01,519 --> 00:36:02,873
- Have a good night, dear.
- Be a good girl.

405
00:36:03,039 --> 00:36:04,677
- Bye-bye.
- Good-bye.

406
00:36:30,360 --> 00:36:31,429
Does anybody live here?

407
00:36:31,599 --> 00:36:34,193
Not since 1963 when it happened.

408
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:36,556
Every kid in Haddonfield
thinks this place is haunted.

409
00:36:36,719 --> 00:36:38,630
They may be right.

410
00:36:56,119 --> 00:36:57,599
- Look.
- What?

411
00:36:57,760 --> 00:37:00,592
- What is that?
- It's a dog.

412
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:09,876
It's still warm.

413
00:37:10,079 --> 00:37:12,309
He got hungfY-

414
00:37:13,599 --> 00:37:15,715
Come on.
It could have been a skunk.

415
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,398
Could have.

416
00:37:17,559 --> 00:37:19,914
A man wouldn't do that.

417
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,956
This is no man.

418
00:37:58,960 --> 00:38:00,518
It happened in here.

419
00:38:00,679 --> 00:38:03,478
She was sitting right here.

420
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:13,157
He could have seen her
through this window.

421
00:38:15,239 --> 00:38:18,119
Standing on the lawn,
he could have seen inside.

422
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:30,791
You must think me
a very sinister doctor.

423
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:33,349
( Chuckles ) Oh, I...

424
00:38:33,519 --> 00:38:35,989
I do have a permit.

425
00:38:37,360 --> 00:38:39,317
It seems to me
you're just plain scared.

426
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:42,552
Yes. Yeah, I am.

427
00:38:42,719 --> 00:38:45,951
I met him 15 years ago.

428
00:38:46,119 --> 00:38:48,269
I was told there was nothing left.

429
00:38:48,440 --> 00:38:52,320
No reason, no conscience,
no understanding.

430
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:55,358
Even the most rudimentary
sense of life or death,

431
00:38:55,559 --> 00:38:59,599
of good or evil,
right or wrong.

432
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:03,195
I met this six-year-old child

433
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:06,119
with this blank, pale,

434
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:08,436
emotionless face

435
00:39:08,599 --> 00:39:11,353
with the blackest eyes.

436
00:39:11,519 --> 00:39:13,875
The devil's eyes.

437
00:39:15,039 --> 00:39:17,509
I spent eight years
trying to reach him.

438
00:39:17,679 --> 00:39:20,148
And then another seven
trying to keep him locked up

439
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:23,391
because I realized that what
was living behind that boy's eyes

440
00:39:23,559 --> 00:39:26,393
was purely and simply evil.

441
00:39:27,519 --> 00:39:28,954
What do we do?

442
00:39:29,119 --> 00:39:31,235
He's been here once tonight.

443
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:33,436
I think he'll come back.

444
00:39:33,639 --> 00:39:35,313
I'm going to wait for him.

445
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:37,641
I still think I should notify
the radio and television.

446
00:39:37,679 --> 00:39:40,911
No. If you do that, they'll see him
on every street corner.

447
00:39:41,079 --> 00:39:42,480
They'll look for him
in every house.

448
00:39:42,519 --> 00:39:46,195
Just tell your men to keep their
mouths shut and their eyes open.

449
00:39:48,719 --> 00:39:50,518
I'll check back in an hour.

450
00:40:02,119 --> 00:40:03,599
"'How now, ' cried Arthur."

451
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:06,148
'Let no one pass this way
without a fight.'

452
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:09,597
"'Is that so?' said the knight
in a bold and haughty manner."

453
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:12,268
I don't like that story.

454
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:14,077
I thought King Arthur
was your favorite.

455
00:40:14,239 --> 00:40:16,277
Not anymore.

456
00:40:18,239 --> 00:40:19,519
Why do you keep them
under there?

457
00:40:19,599 --> 00:40:21,637
Mom doesn't like me
to have them.

458
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,791
"Laser Man."

459
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:26,952
"Neutron Man."
I can understand why.

460
00:40:27,119 --> 00:40:28,952
"Tarantula Man."

461
00:40:29,119 --> 00:40:32,271
Laurie, what's the boogeyman?

462
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,077
( Phone ringing )

463
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:40,432
Doyle residence.

464
00:40:40,599 --> 00:40:41,715
Annie: It's me.

465
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,108
Hi, Annie. What are you doing?

466
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:44,679
Making popcorn.

467
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:48,673
Having fun?
Never mind. I'm sure you are.

468
00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:51,952
I have big, big news for you.

469
00:40:52,119 --> 00:40:53,713
(growling )

470
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:55,791
- ( barking )
- Oops.

471
00:40:55,960 --> 00:40:58,269
- Hold on a minute.
- ( Barking )

472
00:40:58,440 --> 00:41:00,077
Hi, Lester.

473
00:41:00,239 --> 00:41:03,277
I'm about to be ripped apart
by the family dog.

474
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,471
( laughs )

475
00:41:05,639 --> 00:41:08,951
( dog barking )

476
00:41:09,119 --> 00:41:12,954
Lindsey, get this dog
out of the kitchen right now.

477
00:41:13,119 --> 00:41:14,952
(Tv playing )

478
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:24,708
I hate that dog.

479
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:27,474
I'm the only person in the world
he doesn't like.

480
00:41:27,639 --> 00:41:30,632
So what is this big, big news?

481
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:32,159
What would you say
if I told you

482
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:35,233
that you were going to the homecoming
dance tomorrow night?

483
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:37,914
( Scoffs ) I'd probably say
you got the wrong number.

484
00:41:38,079 --> 00:41:42,755
Well, I just talked
with Ben Tramer

485
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:44,512
and he got real excited

486
00:41:44,679 --> 00:41:47,320
when I told him how attracted
you were to him.

487
00:41:47,519 --> 00:41:49,829
Oh, Annie. Oh, you didn't.

488
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:52,992
Please tell me you didn't.
How could you do that?

489
00:41:53,159 --> 00:41:54,833
I mean, how could you
just call him?

490
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:56,273
( Kids laughing )

491
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:58,715
Laufie:
What do you mean it was easy?

492
00:41:58,880 --> 00:42:00,836
I can't believe it.

493
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:03,798
( Kids laughing )

494
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:11,036
Please tell me you didn't.

495
00:42:11,199 --> 00:42:12,952
Oh, you didn't.

496
00:42:13,119 --> 00:42:14,918
- Laurie.
- Oh, I'm so embarrassed.

497
00:42:15,079 --> 00:42:17,070
- I couldn't even face him.
- The boogeyman is outside.

498
00:42:17,239 --> 00:42:19,117
- Laurie, he's out there.
- Hold on.

499
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:21,954
Laurie, the boogeyman is outside.
Look.

500
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:29,871
Tommy, there's nobody outside.

501
00:42:30,039 --> 00:42:32,190
Go watch TV.

502
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:33,878
It's just Tommy.

503
00:42:35,239 --> 00:42:38,436
Oh, please tell me you didn't.
How could you do that?

504
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:42,358
Look, it's simple.
You like him, he likes you.

505
00:42:42,519 --> 00:42:44,351
All you need is a little push.

506
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:48,159
Well, it won't hurt you to go out
with him, for God's sake.

507
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:49,992
Shit!

508
00:42:50,159 --> 00:42:51,911
No, no.

509
00:42:52,079 --> 00:42:53,990
I just made a mess of myself.
I've got to call you back.

510
00:42:54,159 --> 00:42:56,913
Oh, yuck. Lindsey.

511
00:42:57,079 --> 00:42:59,434
I need a robe.

512
00:42:59,599 --> 00:43:02,159
(Tv playing )

513
00:43:05,039 --> 00:43:07,315
( breathing heavily )

514
00:43:20,039 --> 00:43:22,190
( shatters )

515
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:32,630
Annie:
This ain't ever coming out.

516
00:43:35,639 --> 00:43:38,108
(growling )

517
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:41,032
( barking )

518
00:43:42,280 --> 00:43:45,193
Lindsey, Lester's barking again

